thinking you done stole something.

06:23.470 --> 06:25.770
'Cause these kids are
talking about Isiah and Magic.

06:25.970 --> 06:27.190
They don't give a damn about Bruce Jenner

06:27.390 --> 06:30.730
throwing a Frisbee around
in a damn decathlon.

06:30.930 --> 06:32.730
And people don't know
what the hell a Nike is.

06:32.930 --> 06:34.770
What's a Converse?

06:34.970 --> 06:36.230
NBA All Star shoe.

06:36.430 --> 06:37.730
Play like Magic, dribble like Isiah.

06:37.930 --> 06:39.440
That's what it is.

06:39.640 --> 06:41.560
Man, do you know Run-DMC doing
a song about Adidas?

06:41.760 --> 06:43.310
What, who?

06:43.510 --> 06:44.980
Run-DMC making a free song

06:45.180 --> 06:47.020
coming out on their next album
about Adidas.

06:47.220 --> 06:48.350
Who's doing it?

06:48.550 --> 06:50.350
See, that tells me something
right there, Sonny.

06:50.550 --> 06:53.060
Hey, when you signed Moses,
how'd you do it?

06:53.260 --> 06:55.730
Mary Malone. His mama.

06:55.930 --> 06:57.770
I... She thought the world of me.

06:57.970 --> 07:00.230
But, you know, I always
go through the mamas, man.

07:00.430 --> 07:02.310
The mamas run stuff,
especially in Black families.

07:02.510 --> 07:04.270
Man, we need some more players, Sonny.

07:04.470 --> 07:05.900
You got to get me somebody else.

07:06.090 --> 07:07.230
Well, we got Moses.

07:07.430 --> 07:09.230
I know we got Moses, man.

07:09.430 --> 07:11.600
I was up in the club with him
3:00 in the morning last night

07:11.800 --> 07:13.980
trying to get him out of there
'cause he got a 5:00 practice.

07:14.180 --> 07:15.980
I told him, I said,
"Moses, you can't hoot with the owls

07:16.180 --> 07:17.730
all night and fly with the eagles
in the morning."

07:17.930 --> 07:19.600
Yeah, I could not do what you do.

07:19.800 --> 07:21.270
I know you can't do what I do.

07:21.470 --> 07:24.020
You can hardly do what the hell
you supposed to do.

07:24.220 --> 07:25.310
Hey, one more chance.

07:25.510 --> 07:27.060
You want that Adidas suit
from South Korea?

07:27.260 --> 07:28.310
(chuckles) No.

07:28.510 --> 07:29.600
- Better not tell nobody neither.
- No. No.

07:29.800 --> 07:31.940
Phil better not come up
talking about no damn,

07:32.140 --> 07:33.230
"Where's your Adidas suits?"

07:33.430 --> 07:34.980
I need my job, Sonny. Don't play.

07:35.180 --> 07:37.440
Uh, shit, I'm late.

07:37.640 --> 07:40.270
You hit one shot in 30 minutes.
Let's get out of here.

07:40.470 --> 07:42.770
I got to stop by my office.

07:42.970 --> 07:45.020
Damn back and my knees are messing up now.

07:45.220 --> 07:47.060
Hey, Sonny, look at
these damn posters down here.

07:47.260 --> 07:50.060
They upstairs in the running department
got Picassos.

07:50.260 --> 07:51.980
- No.
- We got cartoons down here.

07:52.180 --> 07:53.560
They don't give a damn about our division.

07:53.760 --> 07:56.520
You know, I-I like the, uh...
that new slogan,

07:56.720 --> 07:58.730
the one for the whole company
that they're talking about.

07:58.930 --> 08:00.230
- I don't like it.
- What?

08:00.430 --> 08:01.900
- You know where it came from?
- No.

08:02.090 --> 08:04.650
That damn slogan came from
a convict about to get executed

08:04.840 --> 08:06.350
in front of a firing squad,
and they asked him,

08:06.550 --> 08:08.270
"What's your last words?"

08:08.470 --> 08:09.980
"Just do it"?

08:10.180 --> 08:11.980
- Yeah.
- That's where that comes from?

08:12.180 --> 08:13.520
Yeah.

08:13.720 --> 08:15.440
- Bullshit.
- Dan Wieden told me, man.

08:15.640 --> 08:16.770
He ain't got no reason to lie to me.

08:16.970 --> 08:18.850
Ah, kind of a fitting metaphor

08:19.050 --> 08:21.190
for the way basketball
is viewed at this company.

08:21.390 --> 08:23.730
I know. "Nike.
Just get the shit over with."

08:23.930 --> 08:25.230
- (laughs)
- Ow.

08:25.430 --> 08:27.520
What'd it say about me that I liked it?

08:27.720 --> 08:30.020
That says that you
a fat middle-aged white guy

08:30.220 --> 08:31.400
that don't want to exercise.

08:31.590 --> 08:33.480
That's fair.

08:33.680 --> 08:35.100
(projector clicking)

08:35.300 --> 08:37.310
STRASSER:
So, Mr. Orwell was right.

08:37.510 --> 08:38.730
1984 has been a tough year.

08:38.930 --> 08:40.980
Our sales are down, our growth is down,

08:41.180 --> 08:43.850
but this company is about

08:44.050 --> 08:46.900
who we really are
when we are down for the count.

08:47.090 --> 08:48.900
Am I right, huh?

08:49.090 --> 08:52.440
When you're down on the canvas,
bang, we pop right back up.

08:52.640 --> 08:54.730
Like Balboa.

08:54.930 --> 08:56.230
